<paper id="1480685649"><title>A Logic for Parametric Polymorphism</title><year>1993</year><authors><author org="University of Edinburgh," id="2076549375">Gordon D. Plotkin</author><author org="Digital Equipment Corporation" id="2162106674">Martín Abadi</author></authors><n_citation>156</n_citation><doc_type>Conference</doc_type><references><reference>162591592</reference><reference>326743114</reference><reference>1488646136</reference><reference>1519167703</reference><reference>1543071126</reference><reference>1543392755</reference><reference>1984807151</reference><reference>1998095216</reference><reference>2010663699</reference><reference>2011970877</reference><reference>2105126759</reference><reference>2105950068</reference><reference>2115617817</reference><reference>2135453479</reference><reference>2165657834</reference><reference>2914837968</reference></references><venue id="2758283544" type="C">International Conference on Typed Lambda Calculi and Applications</venue><doi>10.1007/BFb0037118</doi><keywords><keyword weight="0.44408">Programming language</keyword><keyword weight="0.58251">Existential quantification</keyword><keyword weight="0.42255">Computer science</keyword><keyword weight="0.571">Parametric polymorphism</keyword><keyword weight="0.43012">Algorithm</keyword><keyword weight="0.60304">Parametricity</keyword><keyword weight="0.52686">Type variable</keyword><keyword weight="0.56646">Universal quantification</keyword><keyword weight="0.55824">Recursion</keyword><keyword weight="0.4223">Preprint</keyword></keywords><publisher>Springer, Berlin, Heidelberg</publisher><abstract>In this paper we introduce a logic for parametric polymorphism. Just as LCF is a logic for the simply-typed λ-calculus with recursion and arithmetic, our logic is a logic for System F. The logic permits the formal presentation and use of relational parametricity. Parametricity yields-for example-encodings of initial algebras, final co-algebras and abstract datatypes, with corresponding proof principles of induction, co-induction and simulation.</abstract></paper>